perl-Mail-ClamAV
-------------------------------------------
Perl bindings for Clam Antivirus.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.19-4
  clamav-0.88.1-1
  perl-5.8.7-5

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.19-4
  binutils-20050610-1
  cygport-0.1.92-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-1
  make-3.80-1
  perl-5.8.7-5

Canonical homepage:
  http://search.cpan.org/~sabeck/Mail-ClamAV/

Canonical download:
  http://www.cpan.org/authors/id/S/SA/SABECK/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack perl-Mail-ClamAV-0.17-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./perl-Mail-ClamAV-0.17-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/perl-Mail-ClamAV-0.17-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/perl-Mail-ClamAV-0.17-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /etc/postinstall/perl-Mail-ClamAV.sh
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.8/cygwin/Mail/ClamAV.pm
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.8/cygwin/Mail/ClamAV.pm.bak
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.8/cygwin/auto/Mail/ClamAV/.packlist
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.8/cygwin/auto/Mail/ClamAV/ClamAV.bs
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.8/cygwin/auto/Mail/ClamAV/ClamAV.dll
  /usr/lib/perl5/vendor_perl/5.8/cygwin/auto/Mail/ClamAV/libClamAV.dll.a
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/perl-Mail-ClamAV-0.17.README
  /usr/share/doc/perl-Mail-ClamAV-0.17/Changes
  /usr/share/doc/perl-Mail-ClamAV-0.17/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/perl-Mail-ClamAV-0.17/README
  /usr/share/man/man3/Mail.ClamAV.3pm.gz
  /usr/share/perl/cygwin-pods/5.8/Mail-ClamAV.pod

------------------

Port Notes:

----- version 0.17-1 -----
Version bump.

----- version 0.13-2 -----
Rebuilt for perl-5.8.6.

----- version 0.13-1 -----
New upstream release, with support for clamav-0.80.

----- version 0.11-1 -----
New upstream release.  Includes a few bugfixes and uses the 
clamav-config script included in clamav >= 0.73 for setting CFLAGS and 
LIBS.

----- version 0.08-1 -----
Initial release for Cygwin.


Cygwin port maintained by:
http://cygwinports.dotsrc.org/
